I have Classic Shell 4.0.2, running on Windows 7 Pro SP1 (64 bit). I have had Classic Shell ever since I got this Windows 7 computer a few years ago. It is a GREAT program, and I really appreciate it being written.<br /><br />I have two problems related to Classic Explorer. They may have existed since I installed my first version--I really do not know. <br /><br />1. I have added several of your Toolbar Buttons to my Toolbar. When I hover over the icon for most of them, I get a small window that tells me what the Button does. However, the following do NOT display the small window, and they have such a generic icon, that I cannot determine what function they perform: View Details, View Titles, Undo, Redo, Move to, and Copy to. Is there a problem with Classic Explorer here, or is there a setting which I have missed somewhere?<br /><br />2. Your Help says: &quot;After you place a button in the toolbar, you can edit it's attributes. Double-click on the button to edit:&quot; If I double LEFT click, I just get the action (same as single left click). If I double RIGHT click, I get the Classic Explorer Settings menu (same as single right click). At no time do I get the edit screen as shown in Help. This problem exists with ALL of the buttons I have added to the Toolbar.<br /><br /><br />Any help would be appreciated. I searched the FAQ and this forum, and was not able to find anything on these problems.<br /><br />Harry<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=64">ac1210</a> — Fri Nov 15, 2013 10:55 am</p><hr />
